          "text": "## Design Section 2: Communication Protocol\n\nThe web interface needs bidirectional streaming. I'm proposing a hybrid approach:\n\n**WebSocket** (primary channel):\n- Client → Server: Send messages, tool approvals, answers\n- Server → Client: Structured events (JSON)\n\n**Server-Sent Events (SSE)** (streaming):\n- Dedicated endpoint for streaming message chunks\n- Better reconnection handling for long streams\n\n**Event Mapping** (from `AgentEvent` to Web):\n\n| Agent Event | Web Transport | Action |\n|-------------|---------------|--------|\n| `MESSAGE_CHUNK` | SSE | Append text to message |\n| `MESSAGE_END` | WebSocket | Finalize message, enable input |\n| `TOOL_CALL` | WebSocket | Show approval modal |\n| `TOOL_RESULT` | WebSocket | Display result in UI |\n| `ASK_USER` | WebSocket | Show question prompt |\n| `TOKEN_UPDATE` | WebSocket | Update token counter |\n| `STATUS_UPDATE` | WebSocket | Update status bar |\n\n**WebSocket Message Format**:\n```json\n// Client → Server\n{\"type\": \"chat\", \"message\": \"hello\", \"thread_id\": \"abc123\"}\n{\"type\": \"approve_tool\", \"tool_id\": \"tool_1\", \"approved\": true}\n{\"type\": \"answer\", \"answer\": \"Option A\"}\n\n// Server → Client  \n{\"type\": \"tool_call\", \"tool_id\": \"tool_1\", \"tool_name\": \"bash\", \"args\": {...}}\n{\"type\": \"status\", \"text\": \"thinking\"}\n```\n\n**SSE Stream Format**:\n```\ndata: {\"type\": \"chunk\", \"text\": \"Hello\"}\n\ndata: {\"type\": \"chunk\", \"text\": \" world\"}\n\ndata: {\"type\": \"end\"}\n```\n\n**Does this communication approach work for you?**",
